CREATE OR REPLACE TRIGGER databasechangelog_actions_trg BEFORE
    INSERT ON databasechangelog_actions
    FOR EACH ROW
DECLARE
    new_seq  NUMBER;
BEGIN
    SELECT
        nvl(MAX(sequence + 1), 0)
    INTO new_seq
    FROM
        databasechangelog_actions
    WHERE
            id = :new.id
        AND author = :new.author
        AND filename = :new.filename;

    :new.sequence := new_seq;
END;

CREATE OR REPLACE EDITIONABLE TRIGGER "T$MEDIATYPE" 
	after insert or update or delete on CHINOOK.MEDIATYPE
	for each row
	declare
		V_FLAG	VARCHAR(1);
		V_MEDIATYPEID	NUMBER;
	begin
		if inserting then
			V_MEDIATYPEID := :new.MEDIATYPEID;
			V_FLAG := 'I';
		end if;

		if updating then
			V_MEDIATYPEID := :new.MEDIATYPEID;
			V_FLAG := 'I';
		end if;

		if deleting then
			V_MEDIATYPEID := :old.MEDIATYPEID;
			V_FLAG := 'D';
		end if;

		insert into CHINOOK.J$MEDIATYPE
		(
			JRN_SUBSCRIBER,
			JRN_CONSUMED,
			JRN_FLAG,
			JRN_DATE,
			MEDIATYPEID
		)
		select	JRN_SUBSCRIBER,
			'0',
			V_FLAG,
			sysdate,
			V_MEDIATYPEID
		from	CHINOOK.SNP_SUBSCRIBERS
		where	JRN_TNAME = 'CHINOOK.MEDIATYPE'
		/* The following line can be uncommented for symetric replication */
		/* and	upper(USER) <> upper('CHINOOK') */
		;
	end;

    new_seq  NUMBER;
BEGIN
    SELECT
        nvl(MAX(sequence + 1), 0)
    INTO new_seq
    FROM
        databasechangelog_actions
    WHERE
            id = :new.id
        AND author = :new.author
        AND filename = :new.filename;

    :new.sequence := new_seq;
END;
/
-- end trigger;

--create log table trigger
CREATE OR REPLACE TRIGGER databasechangelog_actions_trg BEFORE
    INSERT ON databasechangelog_actions
    FOR EACH ROW
DECLARE
    new_seq  NUMBER;
BEGIN
    SELECT
        nvl(MAX(sequence + 1), 0)
    INTO new_seq
    FROM
        databasechangelog_actions
    WHERE
            id = :new.id
        AND author = :new.author
        AND filename = :new.filename;

    :new.sequence := new_seq;
END;
/

    INSERT ON databasechangelog_actions
    FOR EACH ROW
DECLARE
    new_seq  NUMBER;
BEGIN
    SELECT
        nvl(MAX(sequence + 1), 0)
    INTO new_seq
    FROM
        databasechangelog_actions
    WHERE
            id = :new.id
        AND author = :new.author
        AND filename = :new.filename;

    :new.sequence := new_seq;
END;

CREATE OR REPLACE TRIGGER databasechangelog_actions_trg BEFORE
    INSERT ON databasechangelog_actions
    FOR EACH ROW
DECLARE
    new_seq  NUMBER;
BEGIN
    SELECT
        nvl(MAX(sequence + 1), 0)
    INTO new_seq
    FROM
        databasechangelog_actions
    WHERE
            id = :new.id
        AND author = :new.author
        AND filename = :new.filename;

    :new.sequence := new_seq;
END;
